  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Pilate said unto them, ye have a watch,.... Meaning either the watch of the temple, said to be placed in the tower of Antonia, for the service of it: hence mention is made of the captain of the temple, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 4:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but it is not likely they would remove the temple guards, to watch a sepulchre night and day: or rather, therefore, the soldiers that had had the care of the crucifixion of Christ, and watched him on the cross, are designed: the words may be read imperatively, \"have yea watch\", or \"take a watch\", as the Ethiopic version renders it, and which seems best; for if they had a watch already, what occasion had they to have applied to Pilate for one? but having none, he gives them leave to take one, or such a number of soldiers as were sufficient: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "go your way; as fast as you can, take the watch as soon as you please, make no stay, but satisfy yourselves in this point: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "make it as sure as you can; or, as you know how to do it, and what will be proper and necessary. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "make it as sure as you can; or, as you know how to do it, and what will be proper and necessary. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
